Now comes a snaggy bit: I do not know if my eyes remained always wideopen "in a glazed look of arrogant stupor" as imagined by a reporter who gotas far as the corridor desk. But I doubt very much I could blink--andwithout the oil of blinking the motor of sight could hardly have run. Yet,somehow, during my glide down those illusory canals and cloudways, and rightover another continent, I did glimpse off and on, through subpalpebralmirages, the shadow 